This is the most recent readme-file to xtexcad version 1.3 !!

In order to contribute this package to the Release 6 distribution
of the X Window System, I've made a couple of slight changes 
of which I hope they're improvements.

To compile xtexcad version 1.3 simply create a `Makefile` by 
typing 'xmkmf' in the current directory, i.e. the directory 
containing all the files pertaining to this distribution.
The `xmkmf` utilizes the `Imakefile` - file to create an 
architecture-dependent `Makefile` - file. Now, type 'make all` 
( or `make install' if you've got the permission ) and hopefully, 
in a five minutes time the executable appears.

I've tested xtexcad version 1.3 with release 6 on a NeXT computer 
with the cc compiler (This is a GNU C Compiler !!!).
If you want to install xtexcad on a NeXT computer, you should use
the 'cc' compiler from NeXT! 
Compilation on SPARC's, SUN3 and DataGeneral
has never been a problem with 'CC = gcc' (default setting) !


